{
  "stem": "1169.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everybody was crying, and hugging.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So this was the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So where are the trains?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There is no train there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was the middle of December in north Germany, freezing, but utterly freezing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember the rabbi of Satmar stood next to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he's-- the man who took care of him, what they called his [NON-ENGLISH] hugged him all night from the cold.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was-- his name is, should be well, [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yosef ?] Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yosef ?] Ashkenazi.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He lives in [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Monrona. ?] Finally, 8 o'clock in the morning, the train arrives.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For the first time, we started to believe that it's real.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's a passenger train.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's not cattle cars, a real passenger train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We got on the train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was not heated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But for the first time, we believed it's real.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It took three days to reach the Swiss border.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We arrive midnight to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We've arrived at the border town of St.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Gallen, remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We thought we are in Heaven.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We got on a Swiss train that took us from the border to St.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Gallen.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This train had two qualities that we are just not used to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It had light.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was well-lit.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And it was warm.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It had real steam.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We got to St.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Gallen.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And from the railroad station, they took us to some school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And as we walked, a man who obviously heard that this group is coming, and he broke through the lines and gave an apple to the Rabbi of Satmar.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was very big news, that the Rabbi of Satmar got an apple.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "That's probably the most precious present he ever got in all his life.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
